com.amplifyframework.analytics

Interface AnalyticsCategoryBehavior

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnalyticsCategory, AnalyticsPlugin, AWSPinpointAnalyticsPlugin

    public interface AnalyticsCategoryBehavior
    Defines the client behavior (client API) consumed by the app for collection and sending of Analytics events.

    • Method Detail

      • identifyUser

        void identifyUser(java.lang.String userId,
                  UserProfile profile)
        Allows you to tie a user to their actions and record traits about them. It includes an unique User ID and any optional traits you know about them like their email, name, etc.
        Parameters:
        userId - The unique identifier for the user
        profile - User specific data (e.g. plan, accountType, email, age, location, etc). If profile is null, no user data other than id will be attached to the endpoint.

      • disable

        void disable()
        Disable collection and sending of Analytics Events.

      • enable

        void enable()
        Enable collection and sending of Analytics Events.

      • recordEvent

        void recordEvent(java.lang.String eventName)
        Record the event by storing in the local database.
        Parameters:
        eventName - name of the event. An AnalyticsEventBehavior is constructed based on the name of the event.

      • recordEvent

        void recordEvent(AnalyticsEventBehavior analyticsEvent)
        Record the event by storing in the local database.
        Parameters:
        analyticsEvent - object that encapsulates the details of an AnalyticsEventBehavior

      • registerGlobalProperties

        void registerGlobalProperties(AnalyticsProperties properties)
        Register properties that will be recorded by all the subsequent calls to recordEvent(AnalyticsEventBehavior). AnalyticsProperties registered here can be overridden by passing the same name when calling `recordEvent`.

        Examples of global properties would be `selectedPlan`, `campaignSource`

        Parameters:
        properties - Map of global properties wrapped as an instance of AnalyticsProperties

      • unregisterGlobalProperties

        void unregisterGlobalProperties(java.lang.String... propertyNames)
        Remove specific registered global properties by name.
        Parameters:
        propertyNames - a variable number of property names to unregister

      • flushEvents

        void flushEvents()
        Attempts to submit the locally stored events to the underlying service.

        **Note:** Implementations do not guarantee that all the stored data will be sent in one request. Some analytics services have hard limits on how much data you can send at once. What is the behavior in this case? Naming ??
